description: The Intl API provides language sensitive string comparison, number formatting, date and time formatting, and more.
description_html: The Intl API provides language sensitive string comparison, number formatting, date and time formatting, and more.
name: Intl

deno.notes: Only the locale data for en-US is available.

nodejs.notes: Before version 13.0.0, only the locale data for en-US is available by default. When other locales are specified, the function silently falls back to en-US. To make full ICU (locale) data available before version 13, see Node.js documentation on the --with-intl option and how to provide the data.

edge.notes: Before Edge 18, numbers are rounded to 15 decimal digits. For example, new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US').format(1000000000000005) returns "1,000,000,000,000,010".

ie.notes: In Internet Explorer 11, numbers are rounded to 15 decimal digits. For example, new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US').format(1000000000000005) returns "1,000,000,000,000,010".

edge.notes: Before Edge 18, numbers are rounded to 15 decimal digits. For example, (1000000000000005).toLocaleString('en-US') returns "1,000,000,000,000,010".

ie.notes: In Internet Explorer 11, numbers are rounded to 15 decimal digits. For example, (1000000000000005).toLocaleString('en-US') returns "1,000,000,000,000,010".
